#5623
@@DThe Black Sun Sanctum@@N~
A chamber that predates the pyramid by an unknowable span of time, its walls of
native bedrock untouched by any tool, shaped solely by the terrible slow pressure
of the Black Sun Shard rotating at the room's center for ten thousand years.
The floor is polished smooth by that same rotation.  No torchlight survives here:
the Shard drinks it.  Vision in this room is a memory, a faint impression of shapes,
and the cold is the cold of the void between stars rather than the cold of stone.
The crack through which you descended is the only way in or out; whatever
sealed this place could not seal it completely against a sufficiently determined intruder.
~
