#5616
black_sun_shard shard black sun~
@@DThe Black Sun Shard@@N~
@@DThe Black Sun Shard@@N rotates here, a disc of void-darkness that drinks in all light.
~
Older than the pyramid above it, older perhaps than the desert itself, the Black
Sun Shard is what remains of the sun god's corrupted dark aspect after it was
severed and sealed beneath the bedrock before the first foundation stone was laid.
It is an inversion of solar fire: cold, consuming, and utterly patient.  Every
oasis within a day's travel sickens where its influence seeps upward through the
rock, the water tasting of ash, the palms leaning away from the sky as though
ashamed of the light.  It does not hate.  Hatred requires recognition.  It simply
unmakes.
~
